main event: A Technical Sergeant observed a circular unidentified aerial object maneuvering at a high rate of speed over North Korea on 17 October 1952.
interesting points: The object was observed for 5-10 minutes at an altitude of 20,000 to 25,000 feet.,The object had no visible means of propulsion.,Radar return was negative during the sighting.,The co-pilot reported the object's characteristics were consistent with traditional descriptions of UFOs.,The aircraft and crew reported no unusual disturbances during the sighting.
witness description: Technical Sergeant Kenneth E. Porges, USAF, Co-pilot of a Martin bomber
